The Competition Commission has conduct ed search and seizure operation s at five companies involved in the manufacture and distribution of refined edible oils, baking fats and margarine following allegations of price fixing. The companies are based and operate in Gauteng and Kwa-Zulu Natal. The Commission suspects that five companies colluded in price fixing in manufacturing markets and redistribution. &#8221; The Commission suspects that Wilmar Continental Edible Oils and Fats, DH Brothers Industries, R Waring Holdings, Africa Sun Oil Refineries and Epic Foods have colluded in price fixing in the manufacturing markets and redistribution ,&#8221; the commission said in a statement explaining the raids that took place on Thursday.The cartel conduct includes price-fixing in the market for the manufacture and distribution of refined edible oils including baking fats and margarine, the alleged conduct is believed to have started before 2007 and is still on-going.The search and seizure operation is conducted as part of an ongoing investigation which was initiated by the commissioner, the statement added.The commissioner Tembinkosi Bonakele said they had obtain ed search and seizure warrants from high courts in Gauteng and Kwa -zulu-Natal in terms of section 46 of the Competition A ct. Food and agro-processing is an important focus area for the Competition Commission, and we are determined to root out exploitation of consumers by cartels that are so prevalent in this sector. We have, in particular, been monitoring developments in the fats and oils markets and what we see is worrisome, Bonakele added.-TNA Report